Later this month Moneyweb will be hosting the Better Investor Conference which will cater to all types of investors, with a wide range of topics that will be discussed by top experts in the industry. “We promise to bring you the latest industry insights and trends from the country’s top advisors, chief investment officers, fund managers, as well as experts in private equity, fintech and investments, who will share their perceptions of what’s driving market performances of late, and what they expect for 2022/2023,” Moneyweb said. Some of the speakers at the two-day event include Magda Wierzycka, founder and executive chair of Sygnia,  Busisa Jiya, CEO of the Association for Savings and Investment South Africa (ASISA) and Rish Tandapany, COO for EasyEquities. The conference will take place on June 22 & 23 from 09:00 to 16:00. The event can be livestreamed, free of charge, on Moneyweb.co.za, the Moneyweb App, and the Moneyweb LinkedIn and YouTube channels. “All types of investors, both long-term and novice, will be covering topics ranging from investment mechanics, private equity, property, alternative investments such as cryptocurrencies, risk, tax, fixed income, and more. “Providing valuable insights and tools for all types of investors, this conference will be looking at topics ranging from investment mechanics, private equity, property, alternative investments such as cryptocurrencies, risk, tax, fixed income and more.” Register for the full conference here: https://www.moneyweb.co.za/better-investor-conference/